stats gets 64-bit counters from iptACCOUNT</li><li>changed more bit rate multipliers to 1000</li><li>polished Smoothinfo some more</li><li>ping6 and traceroute are now setuid root</li><li>updated USB and PCI IDs</li><li>libexpat is now built using DESTDIR; the old method shouldn't have worked</li><li>the system RC scripts now use flag files to communicate among themselves</li></ul><p style="margin:5pt 0 0 0"><i><sup>*</sup> Updating dhcpcd and directing startup messages to syslog necessitated changing most of the RC scripts in /etc/rc.d.</i></p><p style="margin:5pt 0 0 0"><b><u>Standard warning</u></b><br />Caution: This update includes changes to core components which will break some old-style 'homebrew' modifications or customisations and may leave your system inoperable. Newer mods which use only the available SmoothInstall methods will likely be unaffected. Check for updates in your mods' threads in <a href='http://community.smoothwall.org' target='blank'>the forum</a> before you apply this update.</p><p style="color:#c00000; text-align:center; margin:5pt 0 0 0"><b>Reboot after installing this update to ensure that all changes take effect.</b></p>|2015-08-21|http://community.smoothwall.org/forum/viewtopic.php?t=42246|20785396
004|--------------------------------|update4-x86_64|<p style="margin:0 0 0 0">Several fixes and enhancements; several packages updated</p><p style="margin:5pt 0 0 0"><b><u>Version updates</u></b></p><ul style="margin:0 0 0 0"><li>linux v3.4.109</li><li>iptables v1.4.21</li><li>squid v3.5.9</li></ul><p style="margin:5pt 0 0 0"><b><u>Fixes and enhancements</u></b></p><ul style="margin:0 0 0 0"><li>If the new kernel doesn't work right, the old kernel can be booted via grub.</li><li>The system's use of the serial console was discarded with Update3. It is at least partially restored; you may need to manually change it if it isn't how you set it if you installed the system via the advanced installer.</li><li>The mpt SCSI driver does not provide ID_SERIAL or ID_SERIAL_SHORT for udev when presenting a logical (RAID) drive to the system; thus a newly installed system would not boot up. This is fixed. If it was a common problem, some other SCSI RAID systems may also start to work now.</li></ul><p style="margin:5pt 0 0 0"><b><u>General system</u></b></p><ul style="margin:0 0 0 0"><li>writeproxy now ensures that certain blank settings are set to 0 (zero).</li><li>gettime.pl now only runs ntpdate if the system has been set to 'periodic'.</li><li>The setup program now displays service pack level and system architecture so the admin can see what she is installing and configuring.</li></ul><p style="margin:5pt 0 0 0"><b><u>UI foundation</u></b></p><ul style="margin:0 0 0 0"><li>dispaliastab now handles toggling 'mark' checkboxes correctly.</li><li>The UPS settings will now be archived and restored when you use the floppy-type backup and restore.</li><li>The 'dial' user will now see the proper time in the UI footer.</li><li>The 'dial' user can now use the trafficmonitor and register (Credits) pages; this error was inherited from SWE3.0.</li><li>The status CGI script will now find mods' 'custom' status scripts. This was an oversight from Update3.</li></ul><p style="margin:5pt 0 0 0">